Package: fastperm
Title: Fast, General Permutation Testing with Sensitivity Analysis
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Jake", "Bowers", email = "jake@jakebowers.org", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides fast, general-purpose permutation tests for arbitrary
    test statistics and as-if-randomized designs, using saddlepoint approximation
    and importance sampling via exponential tilting of the permutation measure.
    Supports Rosenbaum-style sensitivity analysis over the Gamma bias parameter
    with warm-starting across Gamma grids. Intended as a faster, more general
    alternative to brute-force permutation for observational studies, matched
    designs, and stratified experiments.
